        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
                <p>Johns Hopkins University&#44;<lb/>
                Baltimore.<lb/></p>
            <p>Nov. 9&#47;86<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>I remember you expressed a very em&#45;<lb/>phatic disapproval of Prof. Haupts article on<lb/> the &#34;De Profundis&#34; Psalm in the Hebraica<lb/> last year.  And I should like to know what<lb/> you think of an interpretation he has<lb/> given of Ps. 138.  The difficulty seems to be<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; for how could a Psalm ad&#45;<lb/>dressed to God say &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#63;<lb/>  Some of the old commentators took &#91;Hebrew&#93; as<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; and this is suppor&#45;<lb/>ted by the Tarfum&#91;&#63;&#93; which render it &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> Graatz thinks that &#91;Hebrew&#93; stood in the<lb/> text because the LXX renders angels &#38;<lb/> mistook it for &#91;Hebrew&#93;.  Prof. Haupt<lb/> thinks that the Psalms in this case<lb/> is not addressed to God but to David<lb/> or a panegyric on David.  That<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93; throughout is for &#91;Hebrew&#93; <del>&#91;Hebrew&#93;</del><lb/> and it is written by a grateful subject&#44;<lb/> and that from a secular legion&#91;&#63;&#93; the<lb/> compilers of the Psalms turned it into<lb/> a religious hymn as has been fre&#45;<lb/>quently done by modern <sic>complers</sic> of<lb/> hymnals.  In this theory he explains<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; Owing least<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; thy promise greater than even<lb/> thy reputation &#40;caused me to expect&#41; is<lb/> the idea&#45;&#45;one which he asserts would<lb/> be blasphemous if addressed to God.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am glad to hear that the<lb/> Seminary is to be opened in January.  Dr.<lb/> Philipson who was called to Sonnen&#45;<lb/>scheins congregation has had his salary<lb/> raised for 2 to 3 thousand &#38; has<lb/> decided to stay here.  With regards<lb/> believe me truly yours<lb/> Cyrus Adler<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY&#44;<lb/>
                Baltimore&#44; Md.<lb/>
                Please return&#44; if not called for in TEN days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/></p>
            </body>
